   why:"Radio etiquette, PACE planning, and proper comms procedures are tested ROTC skills. Every cadet runs a radio in the field; correct prowords, SALUTE transmission, frequency management, and PACE planning are verified at LDAC and in assignments.",
   howTo:"Learn the NATO phonetic alphabet cold first — it's the foundation. Then build up: radio check prowords, SALUTE reports, frequency setting, net operations, PACE matrix, net-control duties, and finally writing and executing a full communications plan. Reference: FM 6-02 (Signal Support to Operations) covers net management, PACE planning, and comms procedures — use it as your authoritative source for doctrine-level questions.",
